233
00:12:54,041 --> 00:12:55,500
- DON'T MESS WITH US,
LITTLE GIRL.

234
00:12:55,583 --> 00:12:58,166
- ( gunshots )
- ( men grunt, crash )

235
00:12:59,708 --> 00:13:03,291
- UMM, HI.
MY NAME IS MILLY THOMPSON.

236
00:13:04,666 --> 00:13:07,250
LET'S SEE NOW.
I SUPPOSE FOR THE TIME BEING

237
00:13:07,333 --> 00:13:10,041
YOU CAN JUST CALL ME STUN
GUN MILLY. HOW DOES THAT SOUND?

238
00:13:10,125 --> 00:13:11,875
- WE'RE GONNA
LET YOU OFF EASY THIS TIME.

239
00:13:11,958 --> 00:13:14,166
ONLY BECAUSE WE DON'T SEEM
TO HAVE A LOT OF TIME LEFT.

240
00:13:14,250 --> 00:13:16,291
NOW I EXPECT YOU'LL ACT
LIKE A REASONABLE ADULT

241
00:13:16,375 --> 00:13:18,750
AND TAKE CARE OF THEM QUICKLY
WITHOUT SCREWING AROUND,

242
00:13:18,833 --> 00:13:20,208
MR. VASH THE STAMPEDE.

243
00:13:20,291 --> 00:13:22,041
- Men: VASH THE STAMPEDE?!

244
00:13:22,125 --> 00:13:23,750
- VASH THE STAMPEDE?

245
00:13:23,833 --> 00:13:25,583
( chuckles )

246
00:13:25,666 --> 00:13:26,958
- ( rumbling )
- ( yelps )

247
00:13:28,666 --> 00:13:30,208
- ( screaming )

248
00:13:35,666 --> 00:13:36,916
- WELL, MY FRIEND.

249
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:39,041
IT LOOKS LIKE OUR TIME
TOGETHER IS RUNNING SHORT.

250
00:13:39,125 --> 00:13:42,333
THIS SHIP'S TAKING
A REAL BEATING.

251
00:13:42,416 --> 00:13:44,250
I DOUBT
IT'LL LAST VERY LONG.

252
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:47,083
- WELL, WHAT DO YOU WANT TO DO?

253
00:13:47,166 --> 00:13:49,750
HOW ABOUT YOU AND YOUR GUYS
GO DOWN WITH ME?

254
00:13:49,833 --> 00:13:52,250
- I'LL DROP YOU
RIGHT NOW, BLONDIE.

255
00:13:52,333 --> 00:13:54,750
HMM?
- ALL RIGHT.

256
00:13:54,833 --> 00:13:58,208
LET'S FIND OUT JUST WHO SPARKLES
THE MOST BETWEEN US.

257
00:13:58,291 --> 00:13:59,708
YOU IDIOTS STAY OUT OF IT.

258
00:13:59,791 --> 00:14:01,750
WE'LL SETTLE IT
WITH AN OLD-FASHIONED DUEL.

259
00:14:01,833 --> 00:14:03,791
- I'M IN.
AND IF I WIN THIS SHOWDOWN,

260
00:14:03,875 --> 00:14:05,208
WILL YOU STOP THE SHIP?

261
00:14:06,916 --> 00:14:09,625
- IF YOU WON.
- ( grunts )

262
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:15,208
- ENGINE TEMPERATURE
IS AT NORMAL, SIR.

263
00:14:15,291 --> 00:14:17,125
THE HULL IS SCREAMING.

264
00:14:18,625 --> 00:14:20,916
- ALL WE CAN DO AT THIS POINT
IS BET ON HIM.

265
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,458
HE'S OUR ONLY HOPE.

266
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:42,250
- ( chuckles ) I KNOW IT'S
RATHER TRITE AND OLD-FASHIONED,

267
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:44,125
BUT WHAT DO YOU SAY
WE START RIGHT WHEN

268
00:14:44,208 --> 00:14:46,125
THIS COIN HITS THE DECK?

269
00:15:15,250 --> 00:15:16,625
- ( screaming )

270
00:15:21,833 --> 00:15:23,333
- ( clinks )

271
00:15:24,875 --> 00:15:27,708
- ( yelling )

272
00:15:39,708 --> 00:15:42,833
( grunts, thuds )

273
00:15:42,916 --> 00:15:44,958
- ( grunts )

274
00:15:45,041 --> 00:15:46,458
- ( gasps )
- OH NO! VASH!

275
00:15:46,541 --> 00:15:48,333
- ARE THEY BOTH HIT?
- ( cocks )

276
00:15:48,416 --> 00:15:49,666
- ( gasps )

277
00:15:51,166 --> 00:15:53,000
- ( beeping )

278
00:15:55,125 --> 00:15:56,583
- ( both whimper )

279
00:15:58,083 --> 00:15:59,208
- ( gunshot )

280
00:16:00,875 --> 00:16:02,791
- YOU STUPID IDIOT.

281
00:16:04,625 --> 00:16:06,750
THAT'S WHAT YOU GET
FOR JUMPING AROUND

282
00:16:06,833 --> 00:16:09,375
LIKE AN ACROBAT IN
THE SHAPE YOU'RE IN.

283
00:16:09,458 --> 00:16:11,416
- AREN'T YOU GONNA FINISH HIM?

284
00:16:11,500 --> 00:16:13,083
- ( footsteps )
- HEY. BOSS?

285
00:16:13,166 --> 00:16:14,500
- BEREMY, JUST SHUT UP.

286
00:16:14,583 --> 00:16:17,958
I DIDN'T EVEN SHOOT HIM.
HE TORE HIS OWN WOUNDS OPEN.

287
00:16:18,041 --> 00:16:20,250
- YOU SHOULD FINISH HIM,
ANYWAY, BOSS.

288
00:16:20,333 --> 00:16:21,416
YOU'RE TOO SOFT-HEARTED.

289
00:16:21,500 --> 00:16:24,250
HEY, USE THOSE
HUGE DYNAMOS OF YOURS.

290
00:16:24,333 --> 00:16:27,291
- ( chuckles ) LIKE I'VE
MENTIONED SO MANY TIMES BEFORE.

291
00:16:27,375 --> 00:16:29,291
A NAME DEFENDED TO THE DEATH

292
00:16:29,375 --> 00:16:31,500
IS A NAME WORTHY OF RESPECT.

293
00:16:31,583 --> 00:16:33,541
- EVERYBODY, VASH WON THE DUEL!

294
00:16:33,625 --> 00:16:36,458
- ( cheers )

295
00:16:36,541 --> 00:16:38,833
- EMERGENCY BRAKES!
HIT THEM NOW!

296
00:16:38,916 --> 00:16:40,083
- AYE, CAPTAIN.

297
00:16:40,166 --> 00:16:42,125
- ( clanking )
- ( grunts )

298
00:16:43,916 --> 00:16:46,000
IT'S NO GOOD.
THEY WON'T ENGAGE.

299
00:16:46,083 --> 00:16:47,250
- SIR!

300
00:16:47,333 --> 00:16:48,583
- DID THE IMPACT DAMAGE
THE HYDRAULIC SYSTEM?

301
00:16:48,666 --> 00:16:49,958
- UNCONFIRMED, SIR,
BUT I'M GETTING

302
00:16:50,041 --> 00:16:51,708
ABNORMAL PRESSURE READINGS
IN THE BOILER.

303
00:16:51,791 --> 00:16:52,875
IF IT GETS MUCH
HIGHER THAN THIS,

304
00:16:52,958 --> 00:16:54,333
THE ENTIRE HULL WILL EXPLODE.

305
00:16:54,416 --> 00:16:56,791
- FORCE THE ENGINES
TO A FULL STOP IMMEDIATELY.

306
00:17:00,458 --> 00:17:02,333
- ( groaning )

307
00:17:02,416 --> 00:17:04,625
-  I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU WERE
FIGHTING IN THAT CONDITION.

308
00:17:04,708 --> 00:17:06,000
- ARE YOU OUT OF YOUR MIND?!

309
00:17:06,083 --> 00:17:07,750
- WE HAVE TO GET THAT
LOOKED AFTER QUICK.

310
00:17:07,833 --> 00:17:09,708
- WE'VE GOT AN EMERGENCY!
- All: HUH?

311
00:17:09,791 --> 00:17:11,250
- WHAT'S GOING ON?

312
00:17:11,333 --> 00:17:13,666
- THERE'S-- THERE'S BEEN
A SYSTEM MALFUNCTION.

313
00:17:13,750 --> 00:17:15,458
WE'VE LOST THE STEERING!

314
00:17:15,541 --> 00:17:16,666
- ( gasps )
- WHAT?

315
00:17:18,166 --> 00:17:19,666
- WE NEED KAITE.

316
00:17:19,750 --> 00:17:21,875
- IS THERE A WAY
TO SHUT THE ENGINES DOWN?

317
00:17:21,958 --> 00:17:24,416
- WE'D HAVE TO POWER DOWN
THE SYSTEM MANUALLY.

318
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:25,833
- WHERE CAN WE EVEN DO THAT?

319
00:17:25,916 --> 00:17:28,333
- I HAVE NO IDEA.
THIS SHIP IS SO OLD.

320
00:17:28,416 --> 00:17:30,166
- IT'S IN ENGINE ROOM TWO.
- Men: HMM?

321
00:17:30,250 --> 00:17:32,916
- THERE'S AN EMERGENCY STOP
LEVER INSIDE THE CONTROL SYSTEM,

322
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:34,625
BUT ACCESS IS LIMITED.

323
00:17:34,708 --> 00:17:36,666
- WHAT THE HELL DO
YOU KNOW, YOU LITTLE BRAT?

324
00:17:36,750 --> 00:17:38,416
GIMME THAT.
- HEY, WAIT A MINUTE!

325
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:40,916
- SO THIS IS HOW YOU DID IT.

326
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:44,458
DAMN DAMN DAMN!

327
00:17:44,541 --> 00:17:47,208
- DAMN DAMN!
- OW!

328
00:17:47,291 --> 00:17:48,625
- OH!

329
00:17:50,708 --> 00:17:52,166
I'LL NEVER FORGET

330
00:17:52,250 --> 00:17:54,375
WATCHING MY FELLOW CREWMATE

331
00:17:54,458 --> 00:17:56,583
AS HE WAS KILLED
RIGHT IN FRONT OF ME.

332
00:17:56,666 --> 00:17:58,791
I WILL NOT
ACCEPT HELP FROM YOU.

333
00:17:58,875 --> 00:18:00,666
WE WILL STOP
THE SHIP OURSELVES.

334
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,041
- Vash on radio: Kaite.

335
00:18:06,125 --> 00:18:07,208
Kaite.

336
00:18:08,625 --> 00:18:09,916
What are
you gonna do, Kaite?

337
00:18:11,416 --> 00:18:13,333
- QUIT BUGGING ME. I KNOW.

338
00:18:13,416 --> 00:18:16,500
THE TIME HAS COME FOR ME TO PAY
THE PRICE FOR WHAT I'VE DONE.

339
00:18:16,583 --> 00:18:19,791
- Man on voice tube: Only 4,500
yards left till the deadline.

340
00:18:23,375 --> 00:18:25,208
- ( grunting )

341
00:18:27,208 --> 00:18:29,166
- 4,000 yards remaining.

342
00:18:35,875 --> 00:18:39,791
- OKAY, THAT'S IT!
- ALL RIGHT, LET'S GET IT OPEN!

343
00:18:39,875 --> 00:18:41,791
- ( grunting )

344
00:18:45,208 --> 00:18:47,208
- 3,500 yards.

345
00:18:48,375 --> 00:18:50,125
3,000!
- WHERE'S THE DAMN LEVER?

346
00:18:50,208 --> 00:18:53,125
WHAT'S WITH THIS PLACE?
IT'S LIKE A CELLAR IN HERE.

347
00:18:53,208 --> 00:18:55,250
- 2,500!
- LOOK!

348
00:18:55,333 --> 00:18:58,250
IT'S WAY OVER THERE!

349
00:18:58,333 --> 00:19:00,291
- ( chattering, crying )

350
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:04,833
- IT ISN'T WORKING, DAMN IT!

351
00:19:04,916 --> 00:19:06,583
IT WON'T BUDGE!
THERE JUST ISN'T ANY WAY

352
00:19:06,666 --> 00:19:08,291
WE CAN GET THROUGH
THIS MESS OF PIPES!

353
00:19:09,375 --> 00:19:11,833
- 1,800!

354
00:19:11,916 --> 00:19:13,041
- COME ON.

355
00:19:13,125 --> 00:19:14,625
- IT'S HOPELESS! THERE'S
NOTHING WE CAN DO!

356
00:19:14,708 --> 00:19:17,125
WE'RE NOT GONNA MAKE IT!
- CALM DOWN.

357
00:19:17,208 --> 00:19:19,333
THERE'S A WAY.
THERE'S GOTTA BE.

358
00:19:21,208 --> 00:19:22,125
- ( men grunt )
- MOVE IT!

359
00:19:22,208 --> 00:19:24,083
( yells )

360
00:19:25,208 --> 00:19:27,083
- ( hissing )

361
00:19:27,166 --> 00:19:29,250
- ( screams )

362
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:41,291
( grunts )

363
00:19:44,791 --> 00:19:46,833
- ( sizzling )
- ( screams )

364
00:19:54,250 --> 00:19:56,750
- EMERGENCY STOP SYSTEM
HAS BEEN ACTIVATED, SIR.

365
00:19:56,833 --> 00:19:58,375
- HOW MANY YARDS
DO WE HAVE LEFT?

366
00:19:58,458 --> 00:20:00,416
- 800.

367
00:20:02,041 --> 00:20:03,458
- WE'RE JUST GOING TOO FAST!

368
00:20:03,541 --> 00:20:05,416
IT'S TOO LATE!

369
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:07,416
- ( yelling )
- ( engine revving )

370
00:20:17,666 --> 00:20:19,791
- ( gasps )

371
00:20:26,666 --> 00:20:28,250
- ( laughs )

372
00:20:39,625 --> 00:20:42,500
THANKS TO MR. NASTY'S
SELFLESS ACT OF HEROISM,

373
00:20:42,583 --> 00:20:45,833
WE WERE ALL SAVED.
- NEON DID THAT?

374
00:20:45,916 --> 00:20:47,916
- NOW DON'T GET THE WRONG IDEA.

375
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,875
I JUST PAID OFF MY WAGER.

376
00:20:49,958 --> 00:20:53,041
THE NEXT TIME WE MEET,
IT'S NO HOLDS BARRED.

377
00:20:53,125 --> 00:20:55,750
I'LL TAKE THAT LIFE OF YOURS.
COUNT ON IT.

378
00:20:57,083 --> 00:20:58,458
- ( chuckles )

379
00:21:00,041 --> 00:21:03,208
- THAT SMUG JERK LAID IT ON US
REAL THICK ALL THE WAY HOME.

380
00:21:04,958 --> 00:21:06,041
( chuckles )

381
00:21:23,625 --> 00:21:26,583
- ♪ SO... ♪

382
00:21:26,666 --> 00:21:29,833
♪ ON THE FIRST EVENING
A PEBBLE ♪

383
00:21:29,916 --> 00:21:32,666
♪ FROM SOMEWHERE
OUT OF NOWHERE ♪

384
00:21:32,750 --> 00:21:36,458
♪ DROPS UPON
THE DREAMING WORLD ♪

385
00:21:36,541 --> 00:21:39,458
♪ SO... ♪
- THAT SONG.

386
00:21:39,541 --> 00:21:42,125
- YEAH, I KNOW IT'S
AN OLD SONG, BUT I LIKE IT.

387
00:21:42,208 --> 00:21:43,875
IT'S A GOOD SONG,
SO SHUT UP!

388
00:21:43,958 --> 00:21:46,583
- OH. YEAH.
RIGHT, IT'S A GOOD SONG.

389
00:21:46,666 --> 00:21:48,583
- ( vocalizing tune )

390
00:21:50,666 --> 00:21:52,916
- ( Rem vocalizing tune )
- I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.

391
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:55,083
- ♪ FROM SOMEWHERE
OUT OF NOWHERE ♪

392
00:21:55,166 --> 00:22:00,250
♪ DROPS UPON
THE DREAMING WORLD... ♪

393
00:22:00,333 --> 00:22:03,458
- IT'S THE SAME SONG
THAT SHE LOVED.

394
00:22:03,541 --> 00:22:08,333
- ♪ SOUND LIFE ♪

395
00:22:10,166 --> 00:22:15,291
♪ SO, ON THE THIRD
CELESTIAL EVENING ♪

396
00:22:15,375 --> 00:22:17,833
♪ ALL THE CHILDREN
OF THE WALTZ ♪

397
00:22:17,916 --> 00:22:20,458
♪ MAKE WAVES UPON
THE DREAMING WORLD... ♪

398
00:22:20,541 --> 00:22:22,666
- WILL YOU STOP IT?
YOU'RE MAKING ME CRY!

399
00:22:22,750 --> 00:22:26,750
- ( growls ) QUIT MAKING FUN
OF ME, YOU BIG BUTTHEAD!

400
00:22:26,833 --> 00:22:28,500
- Vash: OW!
I'M INJURED HERE, YOU KNOW?

401
00:22:28,583 --> 00:22:30,125
- Kaite: SHUT UP,
YOU FLAKEY SHOW-OFF!

402
00:22:30,208 --> 00:22:31,583
- Vash: WHAT?
I'M A FLAKY SHOW-OFF?

403
00:22:31,666 --> 00:22:34,166
- THAT'S RIGHT.
YOU'RE NOTHING BUT A BIG HAM.

404
00:22:34,250 --> 00:22:35,458
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
"A BIG HAM"?

405
00:22:35,541 --> 00:22:40,625
- Rem: ♪ MAKE WAVES UPON
THE DREAMING WORLD. ♪

406
00:22:41,875 --> 00:22:43,750
- ( theme music playing )

407
00:22:50,666 --> 00:22:52,541
( singing in Japanese )

408
00:24:13,500 --> 00:24:15,291
I MET A LONE MAN
IN THE DESERT.

409
00:24:15,375 --> 00:24:18,875
A TRAVELING PRIEST,
NICHOLAS D. WOLFWOOD.

410
00:24:18,958 --> 00:24:23,083
HE SMILED AND THEN HE TOLD ME
THAT I'M A TROUBLED MAN.

411
00:24:23,166 --> 00:24:25,375
FACED WITH
HIS ALL-SEEING SMILE,

412
00:24:25,458 --> 00:24:27,833
THERE WAS NOTHING
I COULD SAY IN MY DEFENSE.

413
00:24:27,916 --> 00:24:30,750
DID I MEET THIS MAN
BECAUSE I WAS DESTINED TO?

414
00:24:30,833 --> 00:24:34,791
OR WAS IT SIMPLY
BY A SMALL JEST OF GOD?

415
00:24:34,875 --> 00:24:37,583
THE MAN'S NAME IS
NICHOLAS D. WOLFWOOD,

416
00:24:37,666 --> 00:24:40,291
A TRAVELING PRIEST
I MET IN THE DESERT.

